From: Gilly1970 <gilroyscott@hotmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: airoha: don't HW-offload IPv6 uplink flows that need VLAN edit

Narrow variant of the IPv6+VLAN black-hole fix. The AN7581 PPE black-holes
hardware-offloaded IPv6 routed flows that need VLAN tag insertion on the
WAN *uplink* (the GDM2-loopback path, pse_port=2). LAN-side VLANs egress via
a direct PSE port, never touch the loopback, and are reported working on both
HW.1.x and HW.2.x. Only decline offload for the uplink case, keeping
LAN-side IPv6+VLAN and all IPv4/untagged-IPv6 fully hardware-accelerated.

Bailing out with -EOPNOTSUPP keeps the affected flow on the software
flowtable, which forwards it at line rate.

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
@@ -387,10 +387,15 @@
 			if (dsa_port >= 0 || airoha_is_lan_gdm_dev(dev))
 				pse_port = port->id == 4 ? FE_PSE_PORT_GDM4
 							 : port->id;
-			else
+			else {
+				/* IPv6 route + VLAN black-holes on the WAN uplink (GDM2 loopback) */
+				if (type >= PPE_PKT_TYPE_IPV6_ROUTE_3T &&
+				    data->vlan.num)
+					return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 				pse_port = 2; /* uplink relies on GDM2
 					       * loopback
 					       */
+			}
 
 			/* For traffic forwarded to DSA devices select QoS
 			 * channel according to the DSA user port index, rely
